entry.string: Loading image into kind cluster: trading-cluster
kind load docker-image hmm-model-training:6-bc701cf --name trading-cluster kind load docker-image hmm-model-training:latest --name trading-cluster
kubectl create namespace trading-monitoring --context kind-trading-cluster 2>/dev/null || echo "Namespace trading-monitoring already exists"
Updating Kubernetes Job with new image

kubectl get job hmm-model-calibration -n trading-monitoring --context kind-trading-cluster || true kubectl get pods -l app=hmm-model,component=training -n trading-monitoring --context kind-trading-cluster || true
docker images hmm-model-training --format '{{.Tag}}' | \ grep -E '^[0-9]+-' | \ sort -t- -k1 -nr | \ tail -n +11 | \ xargs -r -I {} docker rmi hmm-model-training:{} || true
Pipeline succeeded! Image hmm-model-training:6-bc701cf deployed to trading-cluster (trading-monitoring)
